    "created_at": "2016-08-26T22:57:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-26T22:57:56Z",
    "body": "> I also have this issue. Please re-open, or describe a work-around I can use to know when it's safe to update the menu (since updating the menu closes it if the user has it open)\n\nThe click event does not fire when a context menu is open on mac, https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/307b504eb411add469fb9e9bbf8fea93ece178b9/atom/browser/ui/tray_icon_cocoa.mm#L234-L239\n\nSo this is the current intended behavior, you can explicitly call http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/tray/#traypopupcontextmenumenu-position-macos-windows to pop up the menu when `click` fires.\n"
  },
