    "created_at": "2016-08-27T00:04:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-27T00:04:18Z",
    "body": "One UX issue I've noticed with using `tray.on('click', function() { tray.popUpContextMenu }` is that on both MacOSX and Windows, native contextMenus show immediately on mouseDown, instead of waiting for mouseUp like the 'click' handler does.  \n\nI don't suppose there's a way to make Tray respond on mouseDown?\n"
